-- Trina to Supply 345 Megawatts of Panels for Nevada Power Project
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2013-08-13T14:24:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-13/trina-to-supply-345-megawatts-of-panels-for-nevada-power-project.html
Trina Solar Ltd. (TSL) , the third-largest
solar-panel manufacturer, will supply a 345-megawatt power
project in Nevada owned by  Sempra Energy. (SRE)   Modules for the Copper Mountain Solar 3 farm in Boulder
City, about 25 miles (40 kilometers) southeast of Las Vegas,
will begin shipping in the fourth quarter, Changzhou, China-based Trina said in a statement today. Terms of the deal werenâ€™t
disclosed.  Amec Plc (AMEC)  is expected to finish building the power plant in
the first quarter of 2015, according to the statement. The
project will supply electricity for customers of the Los Angeles
Department of Water & Power and the city of Burbank, California.  Yingli Green Energy Holding Co. and Suntech Power Holdings
Co. are the two largest solar panel makers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
